{
  "computedAt": "2026-04-30T12:39:14.457548Z",
  "pattern": "P37",
  "name": "Beat-to-summary expansion ratio",
  "description": "For each beat in the IWD corpus, compute expansion = text_words / summary_words. Calibrates how much the writer's job is 'expansion of brief' \u2014 directly relevant to the harness's writer-prompt expectations and the planner's per-beat targetWords floor.",
  "rationale": "The harness sends the writer a beat brief (~the 'summary' field shape) and expects ~100w of prose back per beat. If Salvatore's actual brief\u2192prose expansion is e.g. 4\u00d7, but our planner emits briefs at ~30w expecting 100w (3.3\u00d7), we may be under-briefing \u2014 or over-briefing if the corpus expansion is closer to 6\u00d7. This pattern grounds those expectations in real published prose.",
  "methodology": "Pure compute on novels/salvatore-icewind-dale/beats.jsonl (n=2470 beats across 3 books, produced by the corpus pipeline scenes\u2192beats\u2192briefs stages). Word counts are non-whitespace tokens (uniform definition for numerator and denominator). The single 'stakes_recalibration' kind beat is excluded from per-kind aggregates (n=1, not a category) but kept in overall and per-book aggregates. Distribution shape inspected via 14-bin global histogram + a 0.5-step fine histogram in the dense [1.5, 10.0] region with local-maxima detection.",
